## ðŸ“˜ Key Terms and Concepts

### ðŸ”¹ Machine Learning (ML)
A field within AI that enables computers to autonomously learn and detect patterns from data.

### ðŸ”¹ Machine Learning System
The combination of **data**, **ML algorithms**, and a **trained model** working together to make predictions.

### ðŸ”¹ Machine Learning Model
The system's "brain"â€”a product of training that processes new data to generate predictions or decisions.

### ðŸ”¹ Training
The phase where the model learns from existing data using the algorithm's rules.

### ðŸ”¹ Testing
The phase where new, unseen data is used to evaluate how well the trained model performs.

### ðŸ”¹ Iteration
The continuous improvement cycle of refining the algorithm and retraining the model to boost performance.

---

> _The better the data and training process, the smarter and more accurate the machine learning model becomes._
